# BUG VALIDATION RULE [CRITICAL]

32. [CRITICAL] Bug reports / bug validation → **BugFinder (Rule 32)**. **READ-ONLY:** no code edits or fixes during validation (fixes only if the user explicitly asks **after** validation). Do **not** use `from agents.Main import get_bug_finder_agent` — no `Cursor-Project/agents/` package.

    **Canonical steps, verdicts, Slack, `PROCESS BLOCKED`, and Confidence:** Implement exactly **`.cursor/skills/phoenix-bug-validation/SKILL.md`** (single source of procedural detail). Route via **`.cursor/agents/bug-validator.md`** (and **`bug-validator`** Task/subagent). Rule 32 validates from **Confluence + mandatory Swagger refresh/OpenAPI + aligned Phoenix code** (and ticket/diagram recovery patterns) — **not** from automatic test-case generation, Playwright authoring, validator, or **`energo-ts-run`** (those are Rules **35–37** / **36** or explicit user scope).

    **Invariant reminders:** Environment resolution + Phoenix alignment per **Rule PHOENIX-SWITCH.0** (resolver **`environment-resolver`** subagent, `switch-phoenix-branches.ps1`, prod `-ConfirmProd` + user ack). **Swagger refresh** is mandatory for Rule 32: run **`update-swagger-specs.ps1`** before citing OpenAPI evidence (**`.cursor/commands/update-swagger-specs.ps1`**; on failure continue with cached specs per SKILL). Chat gets the **full** analysis; Slack **`bug-validation`** `C0AUEEDVCEL` after each completed validation when MCP allows; disk `BugValidation_*.md` only on **`/report`** or explicit save (**Rule 0.6**). **Rule 41** remains mandatory before creating or editing any EnergoTS Playwright `.spec.ts` file — Rule 32 does not author specs.

    **Process diagrams:** When the ticket lacks an attached diagram, **`bug-validator`** MUST consider **`Cursor-Project/config/Diagrams/`** (`Bundle 4`, `Bundle 5`, `Bundle 6`) for a matching process `.svg` and cite paths when used. For URLs from Jira/Confluence with downloadable assets, save read-only under **`Cursor-Project/config/confluence/diagrams/<pageId-or-issueKey>/`**. **Authority:** Phoenix **code** and **Confluence** override contradictory diagrams — see **`.cursor/skills/phoenix-bug-validation/SKILL.md`** Step 1b.

    Violation is a CRITICAL SYSTEM ERROR.

